.Dd May 25, 2026
.Dt XTC_VERSION_STRING 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm xtc_version_string
.Nd return the xtc library version as a SemVer string
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In xtc.h
.Ft const char *
.Fn xtc_version_string "void"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn xtc_version_string
function returns the xtc library version as a NUL-terminated string in
.Em SemVer 2.0
format
.Pq Dq major.minor.patch optionally followed by Dq -prerelease .
The returned pointer is to static storage and must not be freed.
.Pp
The string always begins with the same numeric components reported by
.Xr xtc_version_components 3 .
This invariant is asserted by the M0 test suite
.Pq see Pa M0_CLAIMS.md No section Bq C3 .
.Sh RETURN VALUES
A non-NULL pointer to a NUL-terminated string.
The string contents are stable for the lifetime of the process and
across all calls.
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bd -literal -offset indent
#include <stdio.h>
#include <xtc.h>

int main(void) {
        printf("xtc %s\en", xtc_version_string());
        return 0;
}
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr xtc 7 ,
.Xr xtc_version_components 3 ,
.Xr xtc_strerror 3
.Sh STANDARDS
The version string conforms to
.Lk https://semver.org SemVer 2.0 .
.Sh HISTORY
First appeared in xtc 0.0.1.
